  "texts": [
    "All embeddings (output tokens and latents) lie on a sphere around the origin.",
    "Token embeddings lie on the equator and are mostly spread out along the x-axis (left/right), which captures language (English left, Chinese right).",
    "The y-axis (front/back) captures concepts, in this toy picture along a 1D \"sweetness\" scale.",
    "The z-axis (bottom/top) provides an extra degree of freedom that can be used to store information about context, language, etc.",
    "A transformer forward pass moves along the surface of the sphere."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}